    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - HEATER AND AIR
        CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING - Heater-Bunk With Standard Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Heater-Bunk With Standard Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper</title>
        <table id="t0806307" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Heater-Bunk With Standard Temperature Control With Pro Sleeper</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.71in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.60in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (592). Move key switch to ignition position and move bunk heater
                                blower switch to low. At harness conn., measure voltage from terminal A to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75AL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At harness conn. (592) measure voltage from term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor conn. in circuit 75-GS to sleeper gnd. stud or 11-GAN to B-pillar
                                ground stud, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (592), pigtail to sleeper temperature control, measure resistance from
                                terminal A to C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9K ohms to 11K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (592) and pigtail to sleeper temp. control, measure resistance from term. B
                                to C with control rotated fully CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. B to C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>39K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (592) and pigtail to sleeper temperature control, measure resistance from
                                term. A to B with control rotated fully CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. A to B</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>39K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective sleeper temperature control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (162). Measure resistance from (592) term. B to (162) term. B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(592), term. B to (162) term. B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install connector (592). Turn key switch to ignition position. Measure voltage from
                                (162) terminal A to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(162), term. A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect connector (162). Does heater box damper door function properly?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Sleeper control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Open top of heater box. Disconnect heater box damper connector (N/L) and with key
                                switch in ign. position, measure voltage from circuit 75L to gnd.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75L, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L) measure voltage from circuit 75L to 75-GL.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75L to 75-GL.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 75-GL, conn. (161), circuit 75-G or 11-G to
                                right dash panel gnd. stud, then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At heater box damper connector (N/L), measure voltage from circuit 75K to ground while
                                rotating sleeper temperature control fully CCW and CW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(N/L), 75K to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Approx. 2V and 11V.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 75K, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect heater box damper connector (N/L), move key switch to ignition position and
                                note if damper door closes completely and opens completely, when the sleeper temp.
                                control is moved fully CW and CCW.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace defective damper motor assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Sleeper temperature control circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
